[SN]TITLE[SN]
Cybercrime experts advise businesses at Glyndwr University

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Police and experts in cybercrime are meeting in Wrexham to discuss ways to tackle the issue and keep people safe online.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Glyndwr University is hosting the first meeting of the North Wales Cyber Security Cluster with local businesses also attending.
Prof Vic Grout said the aim is to meet monthly to share good practice.
Security agency GCHQ said people and businesses could adopt basic cyber security principals to keep safe.
